title: For Sale:  Accurate Arms 2230 Eight Lb Keg
postcontent:

This 7.62x54R rifle was made in 1942. It is the M1891/30 model which means it is longer than the M44. 

This a big strong rifle that will leave you sore after shooting more than 20 rounds. This rifle has no sling but comes with the bayonet & tool pouch (Detached)

 Trade or sell to georgia carry licensed people preferably. 

This rifle has hardly been used. To my knowledge it was boxed up in the soviet union & made available to us capitalists many years later. 

I bought this rifle to start collecting Mosin Nagants because of my love of the design. The inexpensive 7.62x54R round is the oldest military cartridge still in use today. Anyone who was ever heard it incoming or outgoing is sure to remember. 

I know for a fact this caliber is able to leave a long splinter exit wound in a 9-11 inch pine tree. Possibly a larger tree as well. Very powerful. 

ANYONE WHO WISHES TO BUY THIS MUST LEGAL TO PURCHASE AND OWN GUNS IN GEORGIA.

title: For Sale:  AK-47 'G' Kit parts / build kit
postcontent: 1981 Romanian Guard AK-47 7.62x39 'G' kit components for sale. Includes apparently unused / unfired barrel with all components installed, including barrel trunnion. Other parts are all matching numbers except for the bolt itself. The butt stock and handguard upper and lower are black polymer / used, plus I'm throwing in a smooth dust cover that I found that has the same serial number digits. The basic 922r compliance parts are included: U.S. piston / Tapco G2 single hook trigger group / Tapco muzzle brake and a Red Star Arms retainer plate (to replace the wire hook). That adds up to 5 of the compliance parts (maybe six, depending on how you look at it), so the polymer stock set or pistol grip is the variable you can decide on to match your tastes. The stock set included does not indicate the country of origin or manufacture. No receiver included, since this is a kit build and no FFL is required, but you can pick up a flat or an 80% receiver for cheap, or a serialized completed receiver for less than $100 on GunBroker. The kit components have all been demilled to the point of allowing either a screw build or a full rivet build, so it's ready to finish!

title: For Trade:  vz 2008
postcontent:
i have a very nice vz58 czech made century built rifle  it will come with a total of 6 mags these are similar to a ak but a lot better built here is some differances* The VZ 58 has a milled receiver, the AK-47 is stamped.
 * Even with the milled receiver it is almost one pound lighter than a stamped AK-47.
 * The bolt of the VZ 58 stays open after the last round in the magazine has been fired.
 * The VZ 58 has a more natural point of aim and is faster handling.
 * The safety is more ergonomic making a faster first shot possible with the VZ 58.
 * The ejection port is HUGE. There is no chance of an empty case getting stuck in the action of the VZ 58.
 * The VZ 58 gas piston can be removed or exchanged without tools. 
* The alloy magazine of the VZ 58 is half the weight of the steel AK-47 magazine. (.42 lb. vs. .84 lb.)
 * VZ 58 is easier to field strip.
 * The VZ 58 is striker fired unlike the hammer fired AK-47. This reduces the number of parts and possible points of failure . no cash price i want to trade toward a basic off brand ar 15 as long as it functions right text or call for fast response. 1-REDACTED . these are excellent quality wepons and a blast to shoot and also very accurate. . must be legal to own
